schedule.p:
RECOGNIZING the importance of the Convention on the protection
of the European Communities' financial interests of 26 July 1995
in combating fraud affecting Community revenue and expenditure;

RECOGNIZING the importance of the Protocol of 27 September
1996 to the said Convention in the fight against corruption damaging
or likely to damage the European Communities' financial interests;

AWARE that the financial interests of the European Communities
may be damaged or threatened by acts committed on behalf of legal
persons and acts involving money laundering;

CONSIDERING that the exchange of information should not hinder
ongoing investigations and that it is therefore necessary to provide
for the protection of investigation secrecy;

